        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 30 at 9:44PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 944 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles south of John Martin Reservoir, or 23 miles southwest of Lamar,
moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Heavy rain and wind gusts up to 45 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of western Prowers and
southeastern Bent Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
